SIMPLE: mayhem
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mayhem
<hw>may"hem</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[The same as
<ets>maim</ets>. See <er>Maim</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>The maiming of a person by depriving him of the use of any of his
members which are necessary for defense or protection. See
<er>Maim</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Violent disorder, especially such as causes serious
harm to persons or damage to property.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maying</ent>⟦br⟧
